                            <comment id="17428225" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you post the route you use for that hello world, as usually Camel would transfer the SimpleBuilder into another form that gets initialized eager.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17428233" author="henka-rl" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 13:48:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
		from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;direct:GetHello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
			.routeId(BASE_ROUTE_ID + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GetHello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
			.transform(datasonnet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;{ hello: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;world&apos;&lt;/span&gt; }&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.class).outputMediaType(MediaTypes.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE))
			.setHeader(Exchange.CONTENT_TYPE, constant(MediaTypes.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17428611" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 05:50:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay so we have removed the usage of SimpleBuilder and need to do the same for DataSonnetBuilder so its like the others.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17428671" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 14 Oct 2021 08:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For 3.11.x you can create an instance of DataSonnetExpression and configure it, and use the instance in the Java DSL&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
